📉 2. Production Readiness Checklist (Migration to AWS EKS)

This is what real banks/fintech expect.

⸻

🏗️ Infrastructure
	•	EKS cluster deployed in 3 AZs
	•	Private subnets for worker nodes
	•	Managed node groups configured
	•	Karpenter installed (on-demand only)
	•	ALB Ingress Controller configured
	•	VPC endpoints configured (S3, ECR, CloudWatch)

⸻

🔐 Security
	•	IAM Roles for Service Accounts (IRSA)
	•	Secrets migrated to AWS Secrets Manager
	•	Encryption enabled (KMS for EBS + secrets)
	•	No public node access
	•	Security groups tightly scoped
	•	Audit logging enabled

⸻

🚀 Deployment (GitOps)
	•	ArgoCD installed and configured
	•	Helm charts standardized
	•	Git repository structure defined
	•	Auto-sync enabled for non-prod
	•	Manual approval for prod deployments

⸻

📦 Application Migration
	•	All 15+ services containerized and validated
	•	Resource requests/limits defined
	•	Health checks (readiness/liveness probes)
	•	ConfigMaps externalized
	•	No hardcoded secrets

⸻

📊 Observability
	•	Central logging enabled (CloudWatch)
	•	Metrics collection active
	•	Alerting configured (SNS / PagerDuty)
	•	Dashboards created per service

⸻

⚡ Performance & Cost
	•	Right-sizing applied
	•	No over-provisioned pods
	•	Autoscaling configured
	•	Node utilization > 60% target
	•	Log retention optimized

